Knicks  will open the shortened National Basketball Association
season with a game at Madison Square Garden on Dec. 25, the
league said.  The game will start at noon. Other matchups that day are a
rematch of last seasonâ€™s NBA Finals with the Miami Heat at
Dallas Mavericks (2:30 p.m.), Chicago Bulls at Los Angeles
Lakers (5 p.m.), Orlando Magic at Oklahoma City Thunder (8 p.m.)
and the Los Angeles Clippers at Golden State Warriors (10:30
